<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF48FF881D95FD749D0CFBED" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF48FF881D95FD749BCDFBB4" blockId="21.[151,1437,356,1283]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881D95FD749974FC94" bold="true" box="[199,322,752,778]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Smaller (TL: 4.0– 
<quantity id="664DB6BCBF48FF881F5CFD759A50FC95" box="[526,614,753,779]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
), oblong-oval species. Head dark brown, clypeus and anterior part of frons usually paler, reddish; pronotum dark brown, laterally broadly reddish, anterior and posterior margin sometimes reddish translucent; elytra dark brown to black, with paler, reddish brown sides laterally from stria 6. Pronotum with short longitudinal strioles laterally. Each elytron with six complete discal striae and one submarginal stria: striae 1 and 5 beginning slightly posteriorly from base, stria 6 more distinctly so; even striae ending close to apex, odd striae usually shorter, ending more subapically; stria 6 shortest, ending at apical fourth; submarginal stria long, beginning at elytral mid-length and ending at apical fourth (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF48FF881F94FC4C9B2DFC7D" box="[710,795,968,995]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1375,184,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-23@36.[204,1382,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Habitus of Copelatus in China. 21. C. sociennus (♂; Hengqin Island, Guangdong); 22. C. tenebrosus (♂; Hengqin Island, Guangdong); 23. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype ♂; Beihai, Yunnan); 24. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (paratype ♀; Beihai, Yunnan). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411112/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view sickle-shaped, simple, regularly turned in apical half to obtusely pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF48FF881E3BFC689B8AFB99" box="[873,956,1004,1031]" captionStart="FIGURES 51–62" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,193,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[190,1397,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 51–62. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 51, 53, 55, 57, 59, 61. median lobe in lateral view; 52, 54, 56, 58, 60, 62. paramere. 51–52. C. parallelus (Yushuwan, Hunan); 53. C. puzhelongi sp. nov. (a. holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan; b. Huanglianshan, Yunnan; c. Houaphanh, Laos); 54. C. puzhelongi sp. nov. (holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan); 55–56. C. rimosus (Dali, Yunnan); 57. C. rosulae sp. nov. (a. holotype, Pianma, Yunnan; b. Kongshu, Yunnan); 58. C. rosulae sp. nov. (Kongshu, Yunnan); 59–60. C. sociennus (Hengqin Island, Guangdong); 61–62. C. tenebrosus (Hengqin Island, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412783/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Parameres broad, ‘D’-shaped; apex short and broad; apical lobes long, club-shaped (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF48FF881F2AFB949AFAFBB5" box="[632,716,1040,1067]" captionStart="FIGURES 51–62" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[197,1390,193,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[190,1397,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 51–62. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 51, 53, 55, 57, 59, 61. median lobe in lateral view; 52, 54, 56, 58, 60, 62. paramere. 51–52. C. parallelus (Yushuwan, Hunan); 53. C. puzhelongi sp. nov. (a. holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan; b. Huanglianshan, Yunnan; c. Houaphanh, Laos); 54. C. puzhelongi sp. nov. (holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan); 55–56. C. rimosus (Dali, Yunnan); 57. C. rosulae sp. nov. (a. holotype, Pianma, Yunnan; b. Kongshu, Yunnan); 58. C. rosulae sp. nov. (Kongshu, Yunnan); 59–60. C. sociennus (Hengqin Island, Guangdong); 61–62. C. tenebrosus (Hengqin Island, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412783/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Female identical to male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF48FF881D95FBB09D0CFBED" blockId="21.[151,1437,356,1283]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881D95FBB099A8FBD0" bold="true" box="[199,414,1076,1102]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Collection details.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF48FF881CF5FBB09AACFBD0" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1880" box="[423,666,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenebrosus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881CF5FBB09AACFBD0" box="[423,666,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Copelatus tenebrosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits various kinds of stagnant water bodies, especially puddles and small pools with at least some vegetation; abundant in paddy fields; frequently attracted at light traps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF48FF881D95FBF899E3FA9D" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF48FF881D95FBF899E3FA9D" blockId="21.[151,1437,356,1283]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881D95FBF89957FB08" bold="true" box="[199,353,1148,1174]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Distribution.</emphasis>
One of the most widespread 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF48FF881FF6FBF89B46FB08" box="[676,880,1148,1174]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881FF6FBF89B20FB08" box="[676,790,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Copelatus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in the Oriental and Australian Regions, from the Indian subcontinent to 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF48FF881CADFB249A50FB24" box="[511,614,1184,1210]" name="Australia" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF48FF881F26FB249B0EFB25" author="Sheth, S. D. &amp; Ghate, H. V. &amp; Hajek, J." box="[628,824,1184,1211]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" pagination="235 - 260" refId="ref33625" refString="Sheth, S. D., Ghate, H. V. &amp; Hajek, J. (2018) Copelatus Erichson, 1832 from Maharashtra, India, with description of three new species and notes on other taxa of the genus (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Copelatinae). Zootaxa, 4459 (2), 235 - 260. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4459.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Sheth 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881FEFFB259AC0FB24" box="[701,758,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF48FF881E11FB249C19FB25" author="Hendrich, L. &amp; Shaverdo, H. &amp; Hajek, J. &amp; Balke, M." box="[835,1071,1184,1211]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" pagination="81 - 152" refId="ref32494" refString="Hendrich, L., Shaverdo, H., Hajek, J. &amp; Balke, M. (2019) Taxonomic revision of Australian Copelatus Erichson, 1832 (Coleoptera, Dytiscidae, Copelatinae). ZooKeys, 889, 81 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 889.39090" type="journal article" year="2019">
Hendrich 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881EE0FB259BDDFB24" box="[946,1003,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Its northernmost distribution is confined to southern 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF48FF881CD1FB4099F0FB40" box="[387,454,1220,1246]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF48FF881C87FB409A17FB40" box="[469,545,1220,1246]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF48FF881F7EFB419A4DFB41" box="[556,635,1221,1247]" name="Macao" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Macao</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF48FF881FD7FB409AECFB40" box="[645,730,1220,1246]" name="Taiwan" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, Yunnan) and Ryukyus (
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF48FF881EBBFB419C68FB41" author="Sato, M." box="[1001,1118,1220,1247]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" pagination="57 - 67" refId="ref33445" refString="Sato, M. (1985) The genus Copelatus of Japan (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society, 17, 57 - 67." type="journal article" year="1985">Satô 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF48FF88193BFB409D37FB41" author="Nilsson, A. N." box="[1129,1281,1220,1247]" pageId="21" pageNumber="272" pagination="35 - 96" refId="ref33005" refString="Nilsson, A. N. (1995) Noteridae and Dytiscidae: Annotated check list of the Noteridae and Dytiscidae of China (Coleoptera). In: Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (Eds.), Water beetles of China. Vol. I. Zoologisch-Botanische Gesellschaft in Osterreich and Wiener Coleopterologenverein, Wien, pp. 35 - 96." type="book chapter" year="1995">Nilsson 1995</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF48FF881847FB409953FA9C" bold="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">first record from Guangdong</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF48FF881C26FB6C99F1FA9D" box="[372,455,1256,1283]" captionStart="FIGURE 83" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2008,2032]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,1132,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-39@44.[267,1320,1127,1984]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 83. Map of distribution of Copelatus in China Mainland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410823/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="272">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
